description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location –   Jenny Lind Ward,                  Stonebow Unit&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Staff  Nurse (RMN)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 5   &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;37.5 HOURS PER WEEK  - DAYS /NIGHTS ROTATION&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An opportunity has arisen for 2 full time staff nurse post on Jenny Lind Ward at the Stonebow Unit. Jenny Lind is an 8 bedded ward for older people that have been diagnosed with a functional mental illness. We are looking to appoint motivated and dynamic individuals to join our Multi-disciplinary team. Jenny Lind has a supportive and motivated team of staff and being part of that team would allow you the opportunity to develop a broad repertoire of skills to support people that are experiencing acute mental illness but also managing their physical health needs.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please Note Currently Jenny Lind ward into a standalone COVID-19 Screening &amp; Isolation Unit (SIU). In line with Infection Control Principles Jenny Lind provides screening and can accommodate cohort nursing for suspected and/ or confirmed COVID-19 patients that are admitted to the Stonebow Unit. This opportunity offers applicants a unique experience of working with Older People &amp; Working Age Adults whilst they undergo a period of quarantine until they are transferred to their host ward. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are able to offer a rotational post working on all wards throughout the unit for individuals that want to develop their knowledge and skill set. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The current shift pattern will involve you working day and night shifts including bank holidays and weekend working. The day shift is 7:30-20:00 hrs and the night shift is 19:30-08:00 hrs&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you require any further information please contact Melanie Jones Ward Manager on Jenny Lind directly on 01432-364045&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Flexible working arrangements will be considered. Any request will be set against genuine operational requirements and limitations and it is not obligatory for a manager to accede to the request. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
